---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Consent to Personal Data Processing — ProxyCraft" noindex>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-28 pb-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Consent to Personal Data Processing</h1>
      <div class="prose-invert mt-8 space-y-6 text-text-muted">
        <p>Last updated: March 2026</p>
        <p>
          By using ProxyCraft, I freely, knowingly, and in my own interest consent to the Operator
          processing my personal data to the extent and under the conditions described in this
          document and the Privacy Policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">1. Operator</h2>
        <p>
          The personal data operator is Individual Entrepreneur Roman Borisovich Belov, operating
          under the ProxyCraft brand.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">2. Categories of Data</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Telegram ID, username, and display name.</li>
          <li>Purchased subscriptions, activated configurations, and service expiration data.</li>
          <li>Payment history and transaction identifiers.</li>
          <li>Technical data required to provide the service and support.</li>
          <li>Any additional information voluntarily submitted to support.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">3. Purposes of Processing</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Creating and maintaining the user account.</li>
          <li>Providing VPN, Telegram Proxy, and WhatsApp Proxy subscriptions.</li>
          <li>Handling billing, bonuses, renewals, and support requests.</li>
          <li>Complying with legal obligations and protecting the rights of the operator and user.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">4. Processing Operations</h2>
        <p>
          This consent covers collection, recording, organization, accumulation, storage,
          clarification, extraction, use, transfer where required by law or service infrastructure,
          anonymization, blocking, and deletion of personal data.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">5. Duration</h2>
        <p>
          This consent remains valid until the purposes of processing are achieved or until it is
          withdrawn by the user, unless a longer retention period is required by law.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">6. Withdrawal of Consent</h2>
        <p>
          The user may withdraw consent by sending a request to{' '}
          <a href="mailto:info@proxycraft.tech" class="text-accent hover:underline">
            info@proxycraft.tech
          </a>.
          Withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing carried out before the request was received.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">7. Related Document</h2>
        <p>
          Additional details about the scope of processed data, security measures, and user rights
          are available in the{' '}
          <a href="/en/privacy" class="text-accent hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
